HII! 
READ THIS BEFORE RUNNING THE CHALLENGE: important little notes

1. SECURE DEPLOYMENT:
The password and username are NOT in the HTML source code. 
They are securely stored as Environment Variables on the cloud server (Render). 
This requires a running web server (server.js) to function.

2. ACCESSING THE CHALLENGE:
- Public URL: https://osint-ctf-challenge.onrender.com

- To Run Locally: Download all files and use the command: node server.js 
  Access locally at: http://localhost:3000

3. IMPORTANT: COLD START WARNING
Since I am using the free version of the web hosting service:
- If the website receives no traffic for 15 minutes, the server will "sleep."
- The next visitor will cause a "cold start," which means the site may take 3-5 minutes to load the first time. This is normal.
(Hoping to implement a cronjob to automatically generate traffic every 15 minutes to prevent cold starts! Coming soon!)
